spec: dc3286
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(decimal)
docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html
provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html — decimal: Decimal fixed-point and floating-point arithmetic"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 666 (dc3286): __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__ dict-presence checks for decimal types."
    - "Classes covered: decimal.Decimal, decimal.Context, decimal.DecimalException, decimal.InvalidOperation, decimal.Overflow, decimal.Underflow."
    - "Theme: __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__ dict-presence (in-place augmented assignment)."
    - "KEY FINDING: decimal.Decimal does NOT define __iadd__, __isub__, or __imul__ in its own __dict__: Decimal is immutable; augmented assignment (d += x) rebinds the variable to a new Decimal via __add__, not __iadd__."
    - "Decimal defines __add__, __sub__, __mul__, __radd__, __rsub__, __rmul__ (forward and reflected arithmetic) but NOT the in-place variants, confirming immutability."
    - "decimal.Decimal does NOT define __iadd__: false. Decimal is immutable; d += x creates a new Decimal via __add__, it does not mutate d in place."
    - "decimal.Decimal does NOT define __isub__: false. Same reason; d -= x rebinds d to a new Decimal via __sub__."
    - "decimal.Decimal does NOT define __imul__: false. Same reason; d *= x rebinds d to a new Decimal via __mul__."
    - "decimal.Context does NOT define __iadd__, __isub__, or __imul__ in its own __dict__: Context is a precision/rounding configuration object, not a numeric operand."
    - "decimal.DecimalException, decimal.InvalidOperation, decimal.Overflow, decimal.Underflow are exception subclasses with no arithmetic protocol defined in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __iadd__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__iadd__')
#
# decimal.Decimal does NOT define __iadd__ in its own __dict__: false.
# Decimal is immutable; d += x rebinds d via __add__, not __iadd__.
# Decimal defines __add__, __radd__ but deliberately omits __iadd__.
# All decimal classes: false.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

